   <body>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC96ea4a0029fb1005804784b414d9e1d2"></a>Changing the rear brake circuit fluid
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2378"> </a>Unscrew the cap (6) of the rear brake fluid reservoir (7).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_4_009902817.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2383"> </a>Attach a transparent plastic tubing to the bleed valve (8) and insert the other end of the tubing in a container placed on
            the floor.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_4_010402818.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2388"> </a>Siphon off the fluid from the reservoir (7).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2390"> </a>Fill the reservoir (7) with new brake fluid up to the MAX mark.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_4_010102819.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2395"> </a>Press the brake pedal to pressurise the circuit.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2397"> </a>Keep pedal depressed.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_4_010202820.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2402"> </a>Loosen the bleed valve (8) to allow fluid to escape.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2404"> </a>The pedal is at the end of the stroke in lower position.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2406"> </a>At this point, tighten the bleed valve (8) to 14 Nm ±10% and release the pedal; push the pedal once.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2408"> </a>Repeat the operation described above until the old fluid flows completely.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_4_010402818.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/warning.jpg">Warning
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2414"> </a>After eliminating the old fluid from the tank, during the refilling operation always keep the oil level above the MIN mark
         to prevent the formation of air bubbles inside the circuit.
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/note.jpg">Note
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2417"> </a>If you do not have the bleeding tool, also move pistons back.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2420"> </a>Fill the tanks (2) or (7) with specified oil taken from an intact container.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_4_010102819.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/important.jpg">Important
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2425"> </a>During the following operation, the fluid level in reservoir must remain above MIN notch at all times. The end of the transparent
         plastic tubing must remain immersed in the discharged fluid at all times.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2428"> </a>Pull brake lever or push pedal and keep them activated while filling.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_4_010202820.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2433"> </a>Connect the bleeding tool to the front LH calliper bleeding valve (5) or to the rear brake bleeding valve (8).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/note.jpg">Note
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2436"> </a>Follow the manufacturer's instructions when using a commercial clutch bleeding tool.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2439"> </a>Suck with the bleeder and open the bleed valve (8) making sure that the relevant reservoir level does not fall below the MIN
            mark.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2441"> </a>Carry on for the time necessary to bleed all air from the system.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2443"> </a>Close the bleed valve (8) to a torque of 14 Nm ±10%.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2445"> </a>If you do not have a bleeding tool available, connect a transparent plastic tubing to the bleed valve (8) as outlined in the
            draining procedure.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_4_010402818.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2451"> </a>Pull the pedal half way or until you feel system pressure, open bleed valve and drive lever or pedal all the way; tighten
            bleed valve to the specified torque and release pedal.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/important.jpg">Important
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2454"> </a>Do not release the brake pedal until the bleed valve has been fully tightened.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2457"> </a>Repeat the bleeding operation until the fluid in the system is free of air bubbles. To obtain this, after filling, carry out
            bleeding operation working on all bleed valves of the system, one at a time.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2459"> </a>In particular, in order to completely eliminate any air possibly trapped in the highest point of the front brake master cylinder,
            work in the same way on bleed valve (9).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2461"> </a>Then make sure that, with closed bleed valves, pressure actuation by pedal is correct.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2463"> </a>Close bleed valve (5) to a torque of 10 Nm ±10%, valve (8) to 14 Nm ±10% and install the protection cap.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2466"> </a>Level fluid and refit cover (6) on reservoir (7).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_4_010702826.jpg"></center>
      </div>
